>Tracy Butler
Gosh, there's a name that takes me back. She was an avid fan of Archie's Sonic comics in the Aughts and used to work hard to improve in hopes of getting to draw for them one day. Never came to pass, sadly. Now, Anon, it's not a style choice so much that technology improved in tandem with artists like Butler becoming more technically skilled as time pressed on. I haven't seen her art in yeeears now, but she worked hard, endeavoring to emulate artists like J. Axer and other professionals because art is what she wanted to do for a living. I imagine her style now more closely aligns with her original goals.
Granted, the Chochi-esque style that was more normal in those days certainly has its charm. I mention him because I think his style is what comes closest to capturing that.
Are there any other artists around whose current work captures that late-90s/Aughts nostalgic charm?
